1. SRAM Model

File: rtl/sram_model.sv

Features:

256 x 32-bit memory
synchronous write
combinational read
word-addressable memory

Purpose: stores source and destination data

2. APB Slave Interface

File: rtl/apb_slave_if.sv

Responsibilities:

APB protocol handling
register decode
register storage
configuration outputs

Registers:

CTRL
STATUS
SRC_ADDR
DST_ADDR
LENGTH
IRQ_STATUS
IRQ_CLEAR

3. DPU Controller

File: rtl/dpu_controller.sv

Responsibilities:

FSM sequencing
address generation
transfer management
interrupt generation
error handling

FSM: IDLE -> READ -> WRITE -> DONE

4. Top-Level Integration

File: rtl/dpu_top.sv

Integrates:

APB IF
DPU controller
SRAM model

5. Testbench

File: tb/tb_top.sv

Features:

clock/reset generation
APB write/read tasks
SRAM initialization
directed transfer test
data integrity checks
